    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\"><h3 class=\"rd__h rd__h--2\" data-title-index=\"2\"><span class=\"entry-title-inner help-subtle\" title=\"Source: Playerâ€™s Handbook (2014), p62\">Wrath of the Storm</span></h3><div data-roll-name-ancestor=\"Wrath of the Storm\" data-source=\"PHB\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><p>Also at 1st level, you can thunderously rebuke attackers. When a creature within 5 feet of you that you can see hits you with an attack, you can use your reaction to cause the creature to make a Dexterity saving throw. The creature takes [[/damage 2d8]] lightning or thunder damage (your choice) on a failed saving throw, and half as much damage on a successful one.</p><p>You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier (a minimum of once). You regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest.</p></div></div>",
